<TITLE> Army holding own 'Taposh attack probe' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 10 (bdnews24.com)  The army is conducting its own probe into whether any of its members was involved in the recent bomb attack upon Awami League MP Sheikh Fazle Noor Taposh. Any army officials proved to be involved shall face strict legal measures, a statement issued by the Inter-Service Public Relations Directorate said Tuesday. The statement followed reports in the media on Monday and Tuesday suggesting some army officers had links to the Oct 21 bomb attack on Taposh's car outside his Motijheel office. "Any indiscipline is strictly dealt with in the army as per the Army Act," the statement said. "Investigation into the alleged involvement of some army officials in the bomb attack upon MP Sheikh Fazle Noor Taposh is going on," it said. The statement, signed by ISPR director Lt Col Quazi Md Kabirul Islam, also asked media outlets not to run speculative reports. "Army Headquarters sincerely expects that the media will not publish any information about the army without having concrete information," it said. bd
